cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.COMM, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with cooperative protocols for full-duplex relaying with loopback interference, which involves information transmission and processing. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on relay assistance and channel conditions, which are important aspects of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes energy-efficient protocols for relay channels, which can be seen as a control problem in optimizing system performance. 
4. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) - The paper deals with cooperative protocols and signal-to-noise ratio, which are key concepts in communication and networking. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the end-to-end signal-to-noise ratio cumulative distribution function, which is relevant to multimedia applications that require high-quality transmission.
